job.plaincontent:
ManpowerGroup is a world leader in innovative workforce solutions. Every day, we connect more than 600,000 people to 
meaningful work across a wide range of skills and industries helping to power the success of clients around the world.

Production Line Leader

Votre mission

- Ensure the continuous development of the assigned production line, including the organization of regular tours with 
employees to promote constant improvement;
- Ensure the optimal conditions that allow the staff to meet their goals. This is achieved via technical and 
organizational skills as well as through the promotion of individually necessary training;
- Ensure that the approved production budget and the investment plan are respected;
- Ensure the sustainable achievement of the agreed annual targets in terms of cost, quality, schedule, lead-time;
- Responsible for the assigned production line and in particular regarding work conditions, accidents prevention and 
environmental protection;
- Ensures the understanding and proper application of the Q&A&S System and of any other company Policies and 
Procedures, as well as any laws in force.

Votre profil

- Degree in Mechanical Engeneering, mandatory
- Experience in production within an industrial company, preferably gained in Switzerland;
- Excellent knowledge of production processes;
- Leadership and people management expertise as well as problem-solving skills;
- Customer-oriented and team work is required;
- Results-oriented;
- ERP (SAP) knowledge;
- Good communication and interpersonal skills;
- Languages: Italian, English, German as a plus.

